org.rakiura.cpn
Class Place

java.lang.Object
  org.rakiura.cpn.Node
      org.rakiura.cpn.Place
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, NetElement
public class Place
extends Node

Represents a Place in the JFern Petri Net. Place is one of the elementary nodes in the Petri Net graph. Place contains tokens which are kept inside a single multiset structure. A place can also be fused with other places by calling the method addPlace(org.rakiura.cpn.Place). The fused places can be in different nets, but the nets have to be executed by only one simulator, to prevent ConcurrentModification errors. If different places are fused, only one will keep a reference to all the others. This fusionplace is the 'boss'. All other places have a reference to the boss. You can get the id's of all the places that are fused together from a boss-place with getFusedPlacesIDs().

getFusedPlacesIDs

public java.lang.String[] getFusedPlacesIDs()
Returns an array of id's of places of which this place is a boss in a fusion. The id of this place itself is included. This means that if this is not a top fusion place, or if this place has not fused with anything, the number of ID's in the returned array is one.

Returns:
an array of id's of places with which this place is fused.
